comments.body:
@rhatdan Please note that as-is, when installing `buildah` on Ubuntu Bionic as per the instructions and PPA, one cannot even run `buildah --help`, let alone `buildah from`. The package is broken.

And I'm not sure if you caught the `runc` note in this discussion -- the docs specifically say installing via `apt-get` will bring in `runc`, but that's untrue.

This issue is especially relevant as GitHub rolls out its Actions feature, which, for Linux, offers only Ubuntu 16.04 and 18.04, and no other distros. Once this issue is properly resolved (and not before), I recommend a team member to open an [issue here](https://github.com/actions/virtual-environments/issues) requesting that `buildah` be included in as many of their VMs as `buildah` supports.
